  <section class="enterprise-hero"><div class="shell"><p class="os-eyebrow">WHY THIS GETS BETTER</p><h1>Better physician guidance, built without exposing physicians.</h1><p>Every physician decision can improve the next physician's guidance through anonymous, aggregated patterns—not individual profiles.</p><p class="enterprise-status">STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT. Physicians remain free. Individual physician data is not sold.</p></div></section>
  <section class="enterprise-principles"><div class="shell"><p class="os-eyebrow">HOW INTELLIGENCE IS CREATED</p><h2>Useful patterns begin with a protected decision.</h2><div class="enterprise-process"><article><b>01 · ANONYMOUS</b><h3>A physician explores a decision.</h3><p>No identifiable physician profile is created for intelligence products.</p></article><article><b>02 · AGGREGATED</b><h3>Signals only become patterns in groups.</h3><p>Minimum valid-sample standards come before any benchmark or report.</p></article><article><b>03 · TRANSPARENT</b><h3>Methods and limits stay visible.</h3><p>We describe what a signal can show—and what it cannot.</p></article></div></div></section>
